# Zig Documentation via Context7

When working on this project, use the **Context7 MCP server** (`user-context7`) to fetch up-to-date Zig documentation and code examples.

## Library IDs (Context7)

- **Master/latest docs (preferred):** `/websites/ziglang_master` — Zig Language Reference from master branch, closest to 0.15+
- **Stable docs:** `/websites/ziglang` — Zig 0.13 docs, useful as fallback
- **Context7 URL:** https://context7.com/websites/ziglang

## URL fallback

- **Official Zig docs (master):** https://ziglang.org/documentation/master/ — use when Context7 is unavailable or doesn’t have the answer (e.g. fetch or open this URL for language reference, std lib, build system).

## When to use

- Whenever you need to look up Zig syntax, std library API, build system patterns, or any Zig API details — query Context7 **first** before guessing or using potentially outdated knowledge
- Prefer `/websites/ziglang_master` for API lookups since we use Zig 0.15+
- Fall back to `/websites/ziglang` (0.13) if master docs don’t have the answer
- If Context7 doesn’t suffice, use https://ziglang.org/documentation/master/ as a fallback

## Why

Zig is evolving rapidly (we use 0.15+); APIs change between versions. Context7 has the latest docs and helps prevent errors from stale knowledge (e.g. `std.io.getStdOut()` was removed in 0.15).
